## Project structure

```
agentBrowser/
├── pyproject.toml
├── package.json
├── src/
│   ├── cli.js              ← Node.js CDP controller (canonical source)
│   └── cdp.js              ← CDP WebSocket client
├── agent_browser/          ← Python package (pip install target)
│   ├── __init__.py         ← public API
│   ├── _core.py            ← thread-local slots, CLI subprocess wrapper
│   ├── _profile.py         ← shared/run/thread profile management
│   ├── tools.py            ← TOOL_DEFINITIONS + dispatch() for LLM tool calling
│   ├── __main__.py         ← python -m agent_browser setup-profile / login / info
│   └── data/
│       ├── cli.js          ← bundled copy of src/cli.js (for non-editable installs)
│       └── cdp.js          ← bundled copy of src/cdp.js
└── scripts/
    └── google-smoke-test.js
```

`agent_browser/data/*.js` are copies of `src/*.js` — keep them in sync when modifying the CLI.
